WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.587
Bem-vindo ao tutorial final!

00:00:02.587 --> 00:00:05.363
Vamos garantir que você nunca fique sem

00:00:05.363 --> 00:00:07.346
espaço em disco de novo.

00:00:07.346 --> 00:00:09.726
Vamos expandir um repository completo online,

00:00:09.726 --> 00:00:12.503
devolver o espaço excluído ao pool e

00:00:12.503 --> 00:00:15.279
depois ensinar a máquina a fazer os

00:00:15.279 --> 00:00:16.073
dois automaticamente.

00:00:16.846 --> 00:00:18.709
Este é o modelo.

00:00:18.709 --> 00:00:21.505
Cada repository é um arquivo em

00:00:21.505 --> 00:00:23.834
um pool de datastore compartilhado.

00:00:23.834 --> 00:00:26.629
Os repositories podem crescer online enquanto

00:00:26.629 --> 00:00:28.492
os containers continuam rodando.

00:00:28.492 --> 00:00:31.287
Mas excluir dados dentro de um

00:00:31.287 --> 00:00:34.082
repo não libera nada por si

00:00:34.082 --> 00:00:34.548
só.

00:00:34.548 --> 00:00:37.343
O Trim é o que devolve

00:00:37.343 --> 00:00:39.207
os blocos ao pool.

00:00:39.207 --> 00:00:42.002
E uma policy automatiza os dois.

00:00:45.270 --> 00:00:47.942
Fill the repository most of the way and

00:00:47.942 --> 00:00:48.276
check:

00:00:48.276 --> 00:00:49.946
the filesystem is getting tight.

00:00:56.044 --> 00:00:57.047
Quase cheio.

00:00:57.047 --> 00:00:58.552
Hora de expandir.

00:01:01.827 --> 00:01:03.151
Grow it online.

00:01:03.151 --> 00:01:05.800
The encrypted container and the filesystem

00:01:05.800 --> 00:01:08.449
expand while the containers keep running

00:01:08.449 --> 00:01:09.773
— zero downtime,

00:01:09.773 --> 00:01:10.656
zero unmount.

00:01:13.656 --> 00:01:15.550
Quatro gigabytes agora.

00:01:15.550 --> 00:01:17.444
Nada foi reiniciado.

00:01:20.745 --> 00:01:21.960
Verify from inside:

00:01:21.960 --> 00:01:22.770
same volume,

00:01:22.770 --> 00:01:23.984
double the room.

00:01:28.675 --> 00:01:31.600
A aplicação não percebeu nada.

00:01:34.887 --> 00:01:36.245
Now the other direction.

00:01:36.245 --> 00:01:38.623
Delete the big file — but watch:

00:01:38.623 --> 00:01:41.339
the pool does not get the space back

00:01:41.339 --> 00:01:41.679
yet.

00:01:41.679 --> 00:01:44.056
Deleted blocks stay reserved inside the image.

00:01:45.806 --> 00:01:47.385
Liberado dentro do repo,

00:01:47.385 --> 00:01:49.359
ainda de posse da imagem.

00:01:52.689 --> 00:01:55.344
Trim hands those blocks back to the datastore

00:01:55.344 --> 00:01:55.676
pool,

00:01:55.676 --> 00:01:56.008
online.

00:01:56.008 --> 00:01:58.331
This is the step most setups forget.

00:02:01.574 --> 00:02:02.179
Recuperado.

00:02:02.179 --> 00:02:05.205
O pool pode respirar novamente.

00:02:08.501 --> 00:02:10.742
Now stop doing this by hand.

00:02:10.742 --> 00:02:13.357
The policy enables automatic growth up to

00:02:13.357 --> 00:02:14.851
a ceiling you choose,

00:02:14.851 --> 00:02:15.972
plus scheduled trims.

00:02:22.318 --> 00:02:23.330
Policy armazenada.

00:02:23.330 --> 00:02:25.861
A máquina assume daqui em

00:02:25.861 --> 00:02:26.367
diante.

00:02:29.641 --> 00:02:30.979
Read it back:

00:02:30.979 --> 00:02:31.871
auto-grow on,

00:02:31.871 --> 00:02:33.656
ceiling at eight gigabytes,

00:02:33.656 --> 00:02:35.440
trim on a schedule.

00:02:38.778 --> 00:02:40.554
Configurado uma vez,

00:02:40.554 --> 00:02:42.331
esquecido com segurança.

00:02:45.626 --> 00:02:47.971
And the view that ties it together:

00:02:47.971 --> 00:02:49.982
storage health shows every repo's usage,

00:02:49.982 --> 00:02:50.652
the pool,

00:02:50.652 --> 00:02:53.332
and how much copy-on-write sharing is saving you.

00:02:53.332 --> 00:02:54.560
Uma visão:

00:02:54.560 --> 00:02:55.174
uso,

00:02:55.174 --> 00:02:58.243
economia e espaço para crescer.

00:02:59.781 --> 00:03:02.552
E assim encerramos a série!

00:03:02.552 --> 00:03:03.661
Dezoito tutoriais,

00:03:03.661 --> 00:03:06.432
do install ao armazenamento em

00:03:06.432 --> 00:03:07.541
piloto automático.

00:03:07.541 --> 00:03:10.312
Seus servidores são seus de

00:03:10.312 --> 00:03:10.866
novo.

00:03:10.866 --> 00:03:12.529
Obrigado por assistir!
